fono: fono (talk to your computer)
fono:
fono: Fono gives your computer a voice interface: press a key and
fono: speak, and it types, answers, or acts. It's the entire voice-AI
fono: stack (speech-to-text, natural voices, a local LLM, wake word,
fono: speaker ID) in one small binary, local by default, cloud only
fono: when you opt in. No Electron, no WebKit, no Python runtime.
fono:
fono: Ships a per-user systemd unit (fono.service) under
fono: /lib/systemd/user/ — enable with: systemctl --user enable --now fono
fono: Homepage: https://github.com/bogdanr/fono
